law.text:
The objectives of the Kentucky Center for African-American Heritage, through the programs and activities of the center, shall be to:
Educate the public and school-age children on the cultural, historical, political, and artistic contributions that African-Americans have made to the Commonwealth;
Cooperate with the Kentucky Heritage Council, the Kentucky African-American Heritage Commission, and the Kentucky General Assembly on matters relating to Kentucky African-American heritage;
Promote Kentucky African-American heritage by working with educational, arts, and humanities organizations;
Recognize and sanction projects that advance wider knowledge of Kentucky African-Americans' contributions to, and influence and impact on, life in Kentucky; and
Support the mission of the Kentucky African-American Heritage Commission.
